quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,46,"Say, 'I only admonish you of one thing, that ye should stand up before God in twos or singly, and then that ye reflect that there is no ginn in your companion. He is only a warner to you before the keen torment"
  34,47,"Say, 'I do not ask you for it a hire; that is for yourselves; my hire is only from God, and He is witness over all"
  34,48,"Say, 'Verily, my Lord hurls forth the truth; and He well knows the unseen"
  34,49,"Say, 'The truth has come, and falsehood shall vanish and shall not come back"
  34,50,"Say, 'If I err I only err against myself; and if I am guided it is all what my Lord inspires me; verily, He is the hearing, the nigh"
  34,51,"And couldst thou see when they are scared, and there shall be no escape, and they shall be taken from a place that is nigh"
  34,52,"And they say, 'We believe in it.' But how can they partake of it from a distant place"
  34,53,"They misbelieved before, and conjectured about the unseen from a distant place"
  34,54,"And there shall be a barrier between them and that which they lust after; as we did with their fellow sectaries before; verily, they were in hesitating doubt"